      "post_content": "Nope.  \nMonolith redirects only one source of damage, and for instance, if you block with your Pariah'd creature, then used this to redirect the damage unto yourself for {1}, Pariah's replacement effect would automatically apply the damage right back to the creature. You can't respond to a replacement effect like you can to a triggered ability. ",
